question:
Suppose that $A=\left( 
 \begin{array}{rrr}
2 & 1 & 3 \\ 
0 & 0 & 5  \\ 
-1 & -2 & 1  \\ 
3 & 1 & 2 \end{array} \right)$, $B=\left( \begin{array}{rrr}
1 & 1 & 0 \\ 
2 & 1 & 1 \\ 
1 & 1 & 1 \end{array}
\right)$, and $C=\left(  \begin{array}{rrr}
1 & 2 & 0  \\ 
2 & 4 & 1  \\ 
3 & 6 & 2  \\ 
-4 & -8 & 1  \end{array}
\right)$.

Which matrix has the rank $2$ ?
